<Base title="iSPIRT Fellow" description="Nikhil Kulkarni's decade as a volunteer and part-time Fellow at iSPIRT, India's leading software product think tank.">

  <div class="page-header">
    <p class="page-label">Community &amp; Ecosystem</p>
    <h1>iSPIRT Fellow</h1>
    <p class="intro">For over a decade alongside my corporate roles, I helped build India's software product ecosystem as a volunteer and eventually a part-time Fellow at iSPIRT.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What is iSPIRT?</h2>
      <p><strong>iSPIRT</strong> (Indian Software Product Industry RoundTable) is India's leading software product think tank. Not a trade association but a volunteer-driven movement that shaped the thinking and policy behind India's Digital Public Infrastructure, including Aadhaar, UPI, and the India Stack. It has had a disproportionate influence on the Indian startup ecosystem relative to its size.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p class="role-meta-block">Part-time Fellow · May 2006 – June 2017</p>
      <p>I started as a volunteer and grew into a <strong>part-time Fellow</strong>, one of a small group of practitioners who designed and ran programs for India's product entrepreneurs.</p>

      <p>Key programs I designed and ran:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>PlayBook RoundTables:</strong> peer-learning circles for early-stage product entrepreneurs. I designed the format and facilitated sessions, helping founders work through real product and go-to-market challenges with structured playbooks and expert practitioners.</li>
        <li><strong>Product Showcase for the IT Minister:</strong> curated a high-profile event where India's top software product startups presented directly to the Indian Minister for IT. I served as Program Manager, handling curation, logistics, and narrative.</li>
        <li><strong>NASSCOM Product Conclave:</strong> volunteered as Program Manager in 2011 and 2012, one of India's most significant product startup events.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Impact</h2>
      <p>The programs I built and ran supported <strong>thousands of software product entrepreneurs</strong> across India. At a time when product thinking was still nascent in the Indian startup ecosystem, iSPIRT's playbooks and roundtables gave founders a framework for building better products and businesses.</p>
      <p>This work is part of why I care deeply about ecosystem building, having seen first-hand what happens when you create the right conditions for people to learn from each other and grow.</p>
    </section>

  </div>

</Base>

